{"title": "Organ Grinder", "content": "A specific type of Street Performer, the Organ Grinder is a Street Musician who would make a living turning the crank on a self-performing organ (sometimes mistakenly called a hurdy-gurdy), usually with a trained monkey on a leash dancing around\u2014alternatively, the monkey is the one turning the organ, and the human is just there to hold the leash.\n\nMore or less a Dead Horse Trope these days, but expect them to pop up in stories set in the 19th and early 20th century. (They've actually been banned in quite a few cities, both because of complaints about the excessive noise they make and because of copyright violations by some of the musicians.)\n\nSee also One-Man Band. Not related to putting someone's privates in a meatgrinder.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OrganGrinder", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SherlockHolmesVersusJackTheRipper", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/BlackButler", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PrincessTutu", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/BusterKeaton", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheCameraman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/GoWest", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/M", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ScarletStreet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Scarface1932", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Strike", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ThePoorLittleRichGirl", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/MightyJoeYoung", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BatmanReturns", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/PiratesOfTheCaribbeanAtWorldsEnd", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SantaClaus1959", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MysteryScienceTheater3000", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Heidi", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SheDoneHimWrong", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Dillinger1945", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheThinkingMachine", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheLegendOfZeldaOcarinaOfTime", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheLegendOfZeldaMajorasMask", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheLegendOfZeldaOracleGames", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Turgor", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Dishonored